column8: Were you able to complete your task?
column9: Did you submit an order to Scholastic Book Clubs during this visit?
column10: Did you experience any difficulties on the site today?
column11: How likely are you to recommend Scholastic Book Clubs to a friend?

column5: I am always so pleased to use the website and to order things for my classroom and my students.
I love scholastics. I just wish the site was more user friendly.
enjoyed shopping with my bonus points
Always nice to shop for all of my book and teaching needs on Scholastic.  Site is efficient and welcoming each month.  Thank you for being my "go-to" place for teaching needs.

We have been receiving Spanish speaking, migrant students in our class in recent months, and so we have needed to add Spanish language books to our classroom library. Our ICT class also has a very wide range of reading abilities, and so we must order books that are several levels below and above to accommodate every student.
Great company, great books, great service!!!!
This is great! I love how fast I can summit an order and buy a gift card for teacher
Excellent collection of books for beginner readers.
I love ordering books for my kids through the website! Great deals and super easy to order!
An unwillingness by staff to rectify my issue through customer service despite a site error
I have been very pleased with the offers each month.  (I love the 5 pack of the same book for literature groups)  and I can buy multiple copies of the $2 books for groups also.
Very fast and friendly to teachers and staff now that the COVID is gone!
Scholastic website  is easy to work with.
I LOVE being able to order books for my students and myself, especially for the summer to reduce summer slide.
I love Scholastic!! Thank you for being here since I was a kid!
I love this site ! Always a great book selection!
Easy to navigate and place my order.
Book trust is so great for these kids.
Site is easy to use and I enjoy the free books for classroom as well as for Zoe!
Entering the item number as listed in the flyer makes it very easy!
Looking forward to these new books!
Smooth process, as always.  Please never stop distributing the paper handouts.  The website works great but I live vicariously through my kiddos bringing home heavily circled Book Order sheets.
love the site and the books, prices cannot be beat!
I love how easy it is to order books now.
Easy and seamless online ordering experience!
I love these books and the prices and the fact that you can get free books as well as giving the teacher books. It is such a great program!

Thank you for a user-friendly site.  I like the suggestions that appear at the bottom that are grade-specific....it's very helpful.  I LOVE the summer packs at the lower prices...this is AWESOME for me to gear up for a long summer without our teacher :)
The books I ordered for summer reading came in time for the children  Thank you
Ordering should be easy to do and process.
Love how I can enter students name and quickly each item by item #.
I always find great book according to my Childs likes and needs. I ordered books as a child and I like to support the book club.
Love that books can be mailed directly to parents this year!
Fast and easy to complete online orders.  Thank you!
Thank you for all you do!
It's a pleasure for me and my child to choose some books .

Over the years, Scholastic bonus offers for placing orders has diminished.  I have been teaching and using Scholastic for 30 years, and the incentives to encourage students and families to order gets less each year.
Thank you for providing wonderful pricing and variety,
Thank you so much for my daughters' new books, and for supporting our preschool, Scholastic Book Clubs!! :)
I have used Scholastic for the last 23 years!  I absolutely love it and I would reccomend Scholastic Book Clubs to everyone!
The book club part itself of Scholastic's website is fairly easy to use. But I also use My Big World and just navigating to and from the other areas of the website isn't always clear.

I actually said to my husband, as I was filling out the order, that I love this site. My son takes the paper flyers home and we have a great time going through the paper flyers - picking out books, discussing fun new books to consider, etc. Then we order online - as we often like books from multiple flyers and the site makes it SO easy to find the books across the flyers and make a single order. I love that it makes recommendations of similar books, that you can sort by grade, search by author, etc. It's so user-friendly and makes it so fun to explore books!
This has been a wonderful way for my students to obtain books.  The better the price the more students who order.
My orders are always in order the way it should be. Thank you!

FIrst off we LOVE scholastic book time.  Thank you for the programs that you do and the books that you select.   THe only issue we had was the site glitched a couple of times, but we shut it all down and reopened and it seemed to run fine after that.
I have been a valued member of Scholastic Book Clubs for the past 30+ years. Always great selection of book, great prices and wonderful customer service.
I grew up with Scholastic book fairs at our school and hold those memories so dear. I love being able to purchase books AND support my child's classroom.
Teacher friendly!!! Thank you!  Been ordering for almost 30 years now.
I love how fast my last order came.  Thank you so very, very much for all that you do.
Easy to use the website and place an order.THANKS!

I love being able to give a book to each of my students as I have several who are not able to afford them. This allows me to not only share books with them but give them assignments after they have read the book.  Thank you for this opportunity.,
I was able to enter everything just fine.

I have been a Pre-K  teacher for over 20 years.  I have trouble with computers and technology.  I have always had trouble navigating your website.  I love your book club, and the books.  I am getting ready to call a human to place my order.
Thank you for the free shipping on orders.
Thank you for making this hassle free.  I like the free shipping option if mailed to the teacher's classroom!  That is a great bonus!
Thank you for all you do!
Very easy to use and navigate.
Easy to browse the website and check out
This was honestly one of the best user interfaces I’ve worked with in a long time, and I’m a software architect. Well done!!
We love to do a book order
Love the choices for my twins and the price.
My kids love the books and love ordering the Birthday coupons for my kids.
Scholastic Book orders are the best! As a mom of 4 kids and a 4th grade teacher, I am a huge supporter of Scholastic Books!!
I love to order books for my grandson !
Love it! You need fun craft products like glow in the dark ink and sticky stars etc. ❤️‍🔥💯

I've used Scholastic Book Clubs for 30 years. I'm retiring in June and this will be a part of my career that I will miss. Thank you for always striving for excellence and for providing  kids with quality books!
SAFE AND EASIER WAY FOR MY CHILDREN TO SHOP AT THEIR BOOK FAIRS
I love Scholastic and how easy it is to order! I just wish you would go back to having more pages in your flyer.
It is very easy to order books.  Thank you!
I appreciate the Scholastic Book Company offering such great books at prices kids/parents can afford.
I have used the website many times in my years of teaching and love getting books for my students and families through Scholastic!
I like the book selections and great prices.
I love searching for books! I love them!
Always works well.  I appreciate the bonuses.
Love the site!  I enjoy browsing and shopping for my students and daughter.
Easy to look and order books.  Thanks
I an a parent and an educator wondering how I can support my children's classrooms along with my own
Site is easy to navigate & pretty intuitive.
I order for my grandson and he loves these books,  I'm so impressed with his love for reading! His teacher noticed such an improvement in his reading and I credit the scholastic selections offered!
Love your book offerings and your affordable prices/great deals!
Love Scholastic and the rewards my class is able to earn for new book purchases!
I find the Scholastic book club site to be user-friendly.
I like that they just come from school
You never gave any free readings. Ugh you guys are the worst guys never visit this website AGAIN and I mean it!!!
I enjoyed live chat to assist me in using my gift card.  This was my first time on Scholastic Book Clubs.  I am the school librarian and I will be back!

Overall, the website is easy to navigate and to find just the right books for my students.  I appreciate the value packs and discounts as I was purchasing books as an end of the gift for my 2nd grade class.
your site keeps getting better and better
AWSOME BOOKS FOR KIDS HOWEVER I WOULD PREFER IF YOU COULD SPECIFY READING LEVELS.
loaded my son’s ewallet with $35 for tomorrow & it is inaccessible
Enjoy finding new books for my students.
First time ordering books for my grandson.

I love the website. It is very helpful and it makes everything so much easier! I highly recommend this website to all of the educators who are struggling to get books for their students! I was wondering how I can get the catologs mailed to my house instead of the school. That is the only problem I have, but other than that I love it!
Very annoying to find your child's teacher. I ultimately couldn't find any of my children's teachers and gave up.
I had trouble navigating the flyers.
Still working on my order for Summer school
At the end of submitting order message indicated that this site was not secure, is this true?
I would like to get all of the the different flyers that Scholastic has for my grade level.  I have only been getting one.
I only had one student order this time.  I think the $6.50 charge to ship a $10.00 item is too high.
I had a very hard time finding my account number.  The menu doesn't give easy access to you account number.  It used to be much easier to get into the teacher page.

An order placed 5/1 was directed to an apartment building, refused by the occupant and sent back.  It should have been delivered to our school.  today I got a notice that a delivery was completed, looked for it, and then found it wasn't shipped to our school, even though I chatted with someone and verified our school address weeks ago.  I have not changed or updated our school address, so I don't understand why this box is lost again.  :(  Also, we would have many more kids ordering if we were receiving  paper flyers.  We receive a few, but didn't get them monthly, and I'm not sure why.

An order placed 5/1 was directed to an apartment building, refused by the occupant and sent back.  It should have been delivered to our school.  today I got a notice that a delivery was completed, looked for it, and then found it wasn't shipped to our school, even though I chatted with someone and verified our school address weeks ago.  I have not changed or updated our school address, so I don't understand why this box is lost again.  :(  Also, we would have many more kids ordering if we were receiving  paper flyers.  We receive a few, but didn't get them monthly, and I'm not sure why.

My school has submitted a tax free form, but every time I order I have to split the taxes away from the pre-tax amount then call to have the taxes removed. It is just time consuming to do it this way.  When I call in everyone is always helpful, but it is time consuming.
Just a suggestion that it would be nice to see a brief book summary on the quick look option.
The auto submit function was not very clearly noted--my order was submitted without me being able to enter my April coupon and so I had to take the time to make a phonecall to get this cleared up.
Drop down box wouldn't let me go to the selection I wanted. As soon as I moved the cursor the box disappeared.
I kept being told "Sorry, no results were found."
I cannot figure out how to use my points for books.
I cannot find some books I wanted buy.  Hot dog and Boris series.  And I nees more preview of the book.  And if you have more value packs I would like to buy  Thank you.
I cannot find some books I wanted buy.  Hot dog and Boris series.  And I nees more preview of the book.  And if you have more value packs I would like to buy  Thank you.
I just wish there was a larger selection of books available.
The site stopped working and I had to add items again.
Use of site could be better, more user friendly. Would like to be able to view flyer and click on books on flyer to purchase.
I got sidetracked. I still need to place the order.
Would prefer that online orders are not automatically submitted before the due date. I was unable to put in my teacher order and add points.
Sad to see prices going up so much.
I thought I could get a free book, but maybe not.  Unsure.
Your sight can feel extremely busy.  There is often too much information flashing at me and rarely information that I need.
It was hard to sign in.

The website could more clearly show all debits and credits and transactions and tracking numbers on all packages shipped and all the pluses and minuses of bonus points.  When I've made an overpayment the credit balance does not show on my account when I sign into website, but when I call customer service, they can see that I have a credit balance on my account.
I had to pick a different teacher when purchasing because none of my childrens teachers were on the list. Would like a different option for the parents who’s child’s teachers are not on the list.
I was not able to complete the order.  I had to go back to previous page and re-enter my payment information.
Not sure why I received an email stating I should "order now" because I had student items waiting. I cleared everything before summer.
I am confused about the amount of money that is in my account right now.
Disappointing we have to use our bonus the following month, puts more cost on me as a teacher to ensure the bonus criteria is met.  The site is a bit tough when it does respond to the clicks.
Disappointing we have to use our bonus the following month, puts more cost on me as a teacher to ensure the bonus criteria is met.  The site is a bit tough when it does respond to the clicks.

I did not update because I am unsure as to whether I will be using Scholastic anymore. Earlier in the year, I was informed that if I place an order for my classroom and mail it from school, I am responsible for paying the shipping costs, but if a parent orders and has it sent to the student's home, there is no shipping fee. I don't understand this. Why should I have to pay shipping? I would think it would be most cost effective for you to eat the costs of shipping and only have to send a box to one place (the school) as opposed to several? I would love to hear the thinking on this. I called and complained about this at the beginning of the year and was told that there would be follow up but have heard nothing.

I did not update because I am unsure as to whether I will be using Scholastic anymore. Earlier in the year, I was informed that if I place an order for my classroom and mail it from school, I am responsible for paying the shipping costs, but if a parent orders and has it sent to the student's home, there is no shipping fee. I don't understand this. Why should I have to pay shipping? I would think it would be most cost effective for you to eat the costs of shipping and only have to send a box to one place (the school) as opposed to several? I would love to hear the thinking on this. I called and complained about this at the beginning of the year and was told that there would be follow up but have heard nothing.
I am trying to find an inexpensive bundle for my end of the year gifts for students.

The mobile website is a bit clunky but it works! Luckily I had the flyers from my child’s school so I could plug in the item codes but it might have been hard to browse. Then again, maybe most of us do visit scholastic with the codes in hand so it’s all good!!

my order was automatically processed this morning and I had orders over the weekend which were not included. I had to call and have it resolved.  It was combined and all set now. I did not receive an email letting me know this was going to happen despite what I was told on the phone.

I am frustrated  with payment on this site. I have to fight to get my payments applied to my account.   With my own money and with district payments.  Frustrating.  They will tell me it is applied and it requires multiple MORE phone calls to really get it applied.  I KNOW I HAVE PAID TWICE ON SOME PAYMENTS YEARS AGO.   This is not a new problem.  I dread ordering from you.

I do find that there is some confusion with trying to log on as a parent vs and educator.  At one point I made a teacher profile but now as just a parent it keeps trying to switch me and it's very confusing.
I HAD TO RE-ENTER UNDER THE STUDENT TAB WHEN i THOUGHT i WAS ALREADY IN THE STUDENTS TAB.
I was hoping you would have books by Chris Vandusen.
I didn't receive my 100 Bonus points for updating the info.  How long should this take?
Checking student orders and looking at items might get from points

Please expand the selection of books in Spanish for Kindergarten grades. There is a growing number of schools that are beginning Dual Immersion programs. These are research based and are growing in popularity and are in high demand. I encourage my parents to only order and buy books in Spanish and I only promote the Club Leo catalogs.
Had a teacher who was thrilled to see you had a book w/cd set!
I love to use scholastic in my class, but lately, I noticed that there is not enough to offer in Club Leo. My students struggle to find variety in Spanish.
It was tricky updating my grades.  I had to try four times before it saved it.  I also wish it was easier to do a general search of books available.

I wish Scholastic wasn't so quick to include things that go against our Christian religion in the books and materials they offer.  I have stopped offering Book Club flyers and we have moved to another company for our book fair because of so many inappropriate offerings.
I was looking for two books for end of the year gifts that I had purchased from scholastic years ago but couldn't find today.

The website is not as user friendly as it used to be, prices have risen and there are fewer perks for repeat customers. I am also disappointed that there  are FAR fewer choices for 7th and 8th grade readers.  The search function is nearly useless for this age group, as it usually steers one towards younger titles.  Please offer more for YA readers!    ....and as a side note, not all of them read "edgy" literature.

The website is not as user friendly as it used to be, prices have risen and there are fewer perks for repeat customers. I am also disappointed that there  are FAR fewer choices for 7th and 8th grade readers.  The search function is nearly useless for this age group, as it usually steers one towards younger titles.  Please offer more for YA readers!    ....and as a side note, not all of them read "edgy" literature.

The website is not as user friendly as it used to be, prices have risen and there are fewer perks for repeat customers. I am also disappointed that there  are FAR fewer choices for 7th and 8th grade readers.  The search function is nearly useless for this age group, as it usually steers one towards younger titles.  Please offer more for YA readers!    ....and as a side note, not all of them read "edgy" literature.
Not yet...survey came through before I did anything else.
I wish you would go back to teachers getting to spend earned money on current orders and not have to wait till the following month.
I wish that there were fewer commercial character books in the sections where teachers can order books with points. I do not use them in my classroom, although I know parents do order them.
I will be back on to submit my order. later.

I had a class order over $25 in April and received a $10 coupon to spend in May. I went to spend it and was not able to because I did not have an order of $25 or more, I was not given a $10 coupon for my April order to use when I ordered in April and would have used my $10 then when I had a class order of over $25.
Bring back $1 books! I have a grandma of a student in my class that LOVES to buy books for our class. Having books for $1 make it easier for her (and other families) to buy books for their kids.

Greetings!  All fine! Site has improved greatly. I am  looking forward to receiving my iPad bonus gift.! I hope there are no issues. PLEASE remember PR is a territory of the the   USA. and I have a zip code and PO Box where  I receive all my purchases from Amazon by USPS. As a matter of fact I find the USPS a very reliable and safe service. I also receive items with UPS so there should be no issue in utilizing these services for sending me a small item like an iPad.  Thank you!  Mary Palou
This was going to be my final book order but one of the items that was placed by a parent is no long available.  Too bad.
It was as asking me for a student's name
The search function needs to greatly improve.
I want my student (niece) to have a wish list that I can select books to order.
I wanted to look at the book dollar deals and packs and the link wouldn't work
Some of books are sold out already(sad :() and some of my son’s favorite books are not here unfortunately.

Noticed some discrepancies in book prices. Picked a book listed as $5 and added to cart. When I used a promotional code for a free $5 book, my options included the same book but listed the price as $3.  This was for The Magic Treehouse #1.

I wish there were more $1.00 and $2.00 books to buy.   I wish there were more special discount codes to redeem.     I'm also happy to order books and support their classroom teachers as well, but I don't know how to do that with three kids. Today I submitted two separate orders, so that it would directly help two of the three teachers. Not sure if there's a better way or not. Making this clearer for parents with multiple children would be helpful.

It said that the parents selected mail to home, yet it would not let me submit the order until I  selected either the school or MY home address. I am hoping it is delivered to this student because school will most likely be out before the box would arrive.

The only two suggestions I have for the site are:  1) I wish that I could click on the author/illustrator's name to see what else you have that they have written/illustrated.  2) It would be nice to be able to select a book in my cart as the free book ($5 book with the READS promo code).

The books are too expensive to buy as gifts. Scholastic used to be quite a bit cheaper than a bookstore. This is my 37 year to teach and my first year not to give each student an end-of-the-year book.  How depressing!
difficult to find titles i need
I actually tried to order these books maybe two weeks ago or so? And it never processed so that sucked. But I’m glad I was emailed to learn there were still items in my cart.
hard to check a variety  of books had to keep leaving the site,.
I was just looking for ideas for summer support materials for my Kindergartener (almost 1st grader).  Once I find some options, I'll visit again with my son available to make the final selections.

I think it is too hard to just browse books. Also, I feel like the book  quality has decreased. I see the same old books  I already own and very few new ones that I would actually want to get or that my students would want to get. And frankly, some books are stupidly expensive 0 if I can get the illustrated Harry Potter for $25 anywhere else, why would I spend $54 at Scholastic...

This has been very frustrating.  This was the first time I ordered from your company.  I was charged and nothing was delivered.  I checked the site repeatedly and it always showed the books as in transit.  Today I chatted on line and was told that the books were supposedly delivered to the teacher three months ago back in February and the teacher needed to contact you.  Of course, had I been told this back in February I would have inquired form the teacher.  Now I contacted the teacher three months after and she has no idea what could have happened.  I have never had a similar experience with any electronic purchase.  I will never use your company again.
I wish there was a 'remember me on this device" option as it's not so great signing in everytime.

I know that costs have increased everywhere but I never expected to see such an increase for so long in the books you offer.  Will you ever return to $5 books as the norm, not $6 and $8.  It's hard to stomach  $6-$8 for a softcover book in my opinion but I need reading material for my son for the summer.
I would love to be able to have different accounts for my 2 sons under the same profile page and I could order online from 1 spot vs 2.
Perhaps you should not hav a capital I next to numbers in a coupon code.
Couldn't find anything that my son would like that was a good price. The multiple flyers and sites is confusing and I often browse and just give up.
I wish there were more suggestions listed when using book finder. A lot of the time the books listed are ones we already have.
Where can I request paper flyers that can be sent home?
Flyers would not load, tried the Click Here if there are problems, but it did not do anything.
Pop up glitches when I went to select a free book … not mobile friendly

The other day, I utilized the chat to ask a question about the promotion. I was responded with very negative and unsatisfied messages. Then, the agent disconnected me as I was asking a follow-up question. Although, I am always amazed with the different features on the website and Scholastic Book orders, I am very disappointed with Scholastic's customer service.
I clicked on order status and received this survey instead.  When I paused to check again, I couldn't find where I should look.

What does "shipment null" mean?   And when an order is placed shouldn't the teacher receive an email if it is no longer in stock?  I have tried to use my bonus points to put books in our school's book machine and I have never had such difficulty or miscommunication in my 35 years of teaching.
I was unable to login to my account. I chatted with 2 people who did not help at all. Then, I was connected to Shelia and she fixed everything! She was helpful and had a great sense of humor!!

The e-wallet is extremely difficult to find on your site. It should be located either on the student's profile page and or on the payment option page. There were too many hoops to finally get to the e-wallet page and it does not link to my stored credit card information, which is inconvenient when I am at work and do not have my credit card information on file.     In short the e-wallet should be more accessible with either a tab, option on the payment option page, and or in the student's profile page. It should also link to the payment options that are already on file.
Sometimes I can't scroll all the way down to review books from flyers.

It is a little confusing that I had one student who placed an online order but it didn't appear on my page when I was doing my order. It did appear last time so, I was confused on that. I would like to be able to see that and see how my points are added when I have an online order.

Was hoping to be able to purchase book splat the cat: Whale of a tale but it's only available in a multipack . Son wanted three books. Two of which were only available in multi packs so I only chose the crab mutlipack this time around. We love all the books and choices though. There's more than enough other options.
It can be hard to find things, like the home page.
I was unable to order my teacher order with the bonus points and the free $$ amount of books.  Very confusing.

When I placed a book into my cart, Iwas unable to get back to the same page.  The back arrow took me to the initial page.      As a retired teacher, with lots of Scholastic experience, I think it will be fun for me to now shop for my grandchildren, while helping out a classroom/
I wish there were a way to fix/ cancel an order that was the wrong book. But the customer service rep was amazing and helpful!
It would be nice if you could add a book then have an options to make it the free book instead of having to search for it.
Would LOVE to get paper order forms. Our orders are bigger on the months that it is handed to the parents. Too easy to forget if not visual.
I wish books were separated by price and point value. It would make shopping easier for the teachers.
The website is not user friendly, requires you to press the "back" button multiple times to complete a simple search.
There was no way to change the classroom teacher's name on the order.  I can contact my grandchildren's teachers to give them a heads up that books are coming to tjem for my girls.

I was just checking to see if any parents have submitted an online order.   Then I decided to update my account for next year.      I do have to say the quality of books has definitely gone down and I couldn't even find one good book to use my bonus points on.  Please get better books, not just gimick/tv series/etc books.
Unorganized and can’t see all the books just a few
1) Not enough quality non-fiction books.  2) I have no idea if my student's teacher is going to submit an order. Seems like that needs to happen in order for us to receive the books?

I received a coupon for $10.00 to use in May from my April order.  The site would not let me use it because I needed an order of $25.00 to use the coupon.  I think this is not right considering we spent over 25.00 last month.  It should be we get to pick books out for $10.00.
It is a little bit hard to navigate, specifically with book clubs. Additionally we have students aged 5-12 in our class so a more multi grade digital order would be great.

It is a little confusing that I had one student who placed an online order but it didn't appear on my page when I was doing my order. It did appear last time so, I was confused on that. I would like to be able to see that and see how my points are added when I have an online order.
It took a lot of time to get some books.
I saw a big bundle a couple of days ago - all the Bob Books for $139 but I can't find it now.  I will keep looking

It is a little confusing that I had one student who placed an online order but it didn't appear on my page when I was doing my order. It did appear last time so, I was confused on that. I would like to be able to see that and see how my points are added when I have an online order.
would not take bonus point coupon advertised on the site
I could not bring up my orders,Maastricht or present. The site was glitchy and I kept having to refresh.
Some books they do a good job & provide enough pages to view to get a good idea of the book others there's only 1 page available...definitely not enough to decide whether to purchase or not.
Difficult to navigate site, browsing is over complicated
Not finding items listed under the item number from the catalog
I cant find any high level of reading books except YA which is way to old for my child.
Sometimes it is hard to get to the Teacher' s page... I have to toggle through so many pages, it gets frustrating.

I understand inflation happens but it's really hard for teachers who want to provide books for their students when the cheapest books have doubled in price. I would love to see the dollar books come back without having had to spend $100 first.
It worked well on my computer. I was not able to get to the  bonus part on my phone.
I do not like how bonus points are awarded now.  I liked using them when they were earned.

I had shopped and was almost done with picking out books when I had to stop for a moment. When I came back I had noticed that none of the items were in my shopping cart and I had been signed in. Luckily the recent viewed showed half of them so I didn't have to review the flyers in great detail again.

We need some books that are actual AR books, for higher level students. We have kids in 5th grade reading on a 9-12th grade level. The content in this area is not great for a 5th grader. We need a better selection please.

I went many months before I noticed my golden apple rewards. I think it would be nice for them to be visible during checkout or automatic is even better.     The book of the month is hard to find. I searched it.

I went many months before I noticed my golden apple rewards. I think it would be nice for them to be visible during checkout or automatic is even better.     The book of the month is hard to find. I searched it.
Could not find a book. Opened up a separate window and was able to put book in cart, but when I tried to add it again, it would not let me add it. Happened about 3-4 times.
